This file contains all the project dependencies and scripts for your Next.js application. 

- The `scripts` section allows you to run commands for developing, building, and starting the project. It also includes scripts for linting and testing your code.
- The `dependencies` section lists all the libraries that your application needs to run. These include Next.js, React, and Styled Components.
- The `devDependencies` section lists all the libraries that are needed for development but are not needed when the application is running in production. These include TypeScript, Jest (for testing), and ESLint (for enforcing code style). The type definitions for React and Styled Components are also included here.
- The `jest` section is where you configure Jest, the testing library.